<body>
    <h1>Zesty Lemon Cheesecake Bars</h1>
    
    <p class="intro">These bright and creamy lemon cheesecake bars combine a buttery graham cracker crust with a tangy lemon filling for the perfect balance of sweet and tart. They're perfect for spring gatherings, summer picnics, or anytime you need a refreshing dessert!</p>
    
    <img src="https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/labs/recipe.jpg" alt="Delicious lemon cheesecake bars with a golden crust and creamy filling topped with lemon zest">
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="highlight">Graham Cracker Crust:</span> 2 cups graham cracker crumbs, 1/3 cup sugar, 1/2 cup melted butter</li>
            <li><span class="highlight">Cheesecake Filling:</span> 3 packages (8 oz each) cream cheese, softened to room temperature</li>
            <li><span class="highlight">Sweetener:</span> 1 cup granulated sugar</li>
            <li><span class="highlight">Eggs:</span> 3 large eggs, at room temperature</li>
            <li><span class="highlight">Lemon Flavoring:</span> 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice, 2 tablespoons lemon zest</li>
            <li><span class="highlight">Other:</span> 1 teaspoon vanilla extract, 1/4 teaspoon salt</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Preheat your oven to 325°F (165°C). Line a 9×13-inch baking pan with parchment paper, leaving some overhang on the sides for easy removal.</li>
            <li>Make the crust by combining graham cracker crumbs, sugar, and melted butter in a bowl. Press the mixture firmly into the bottom of the prepared pan. Bake for 10 minutes, then remove and let cool while preparing the filling.</li>
            <li>In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese until smooth and creamy. Add the sugar and continue beating until well combined.</li>
            <li>Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in the lemon juice, lemon zest, vanilla extract, and salt until just combined. Be careful not to overmix.</li>
            <li>Pour the cheesecake filling over the cooled crust and spread evenly. Tap the pan gently on the counter to remove any air bubbles.</li>
            <li>Bake for 35-40 minutes, or until the edges are set but the center still has a slight jiggle. Turn off the oven, crack the door open, and let the cheesecake cool in the oven for 1 hour.</li>
            <li>Remove from the oven and cool completely at room temperature, then refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.</li>
            <li>Use the parchment paper overhang to lift the cheesecake out of the pan. Cut into bars, garnish with additional lemon zest if desired, and serve chilled.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
